09/02/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- A delegation of Greek Cypriot opposition representatives is expected to pay a historic visit to Turkey within days, according to media reports in Ankara on Wednesday (9 February). The ruling Justice and Development Party invited the delegation, which includes the leader of the Democratic Rally Party (DISI), Nikos Anastasiadis. Last April, DISI backed a UN plan for reunification of the divided island, which was rejected in a nationwide referendum. 
In other news, Greek Justice Minister Anastasis Papaligouras arrives Wednesday for a three-day visit to Turkey, at the invitation of his counterpart Cemil Cicek. (NTV - 09/02/05; MPA - 08/02/05) 
